@Pomac @BlogXilla I didn't discount his work, I discounted an apples to oranges cultural analogy. That's all. 

We can agree to disagree and both move on with our afternoons. 

I only have 7hrs left until @nbcsnl and this vibe isn't helping me at all.

@Pomac @BlogXilla Race is an oppression construct, agreed. 

Unfortunately even Black America is not a monolithic population. I went to Howard, where I saw the whole African Diaspora on the Yard on a daily basis. 

We divide ourselves as well, sometimes even better than other cultures do.

@Pomac @BlogXilla Do you know anyone whose skin is actually BLACK or are they just very very very dark Brown? 

Just like "White" people aren't as white as printer paper are they? 

Race is about class when it comes down to it. Ever heard of Apartheid?

@BlogXilla Xilla, African and Black are not the same. Black is specific to America, Africa is a whole continent. 

This piece of well understood geographical context was brought to you by the Atlas. 

Because when the world gets too big for you, you should open an Atlas. https://t.co/fNW5honnuX
